.TH "gpiod_get_array_value_cansleep" 9 "gpiod_get_array_value_cansleep" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_get_array_value_cansleep \- read values from an array of GPIOs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiod_get_array_value_cansleep
.BI "(unsigned int array_size "  ","
.BI "struct gpio_desc **desc_array "  ","
.BI "struct gpio_array *array_info "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *value_bitmap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "array_size" 12
number of elements in the descriptor array / value bitmap
.IP "desc_array" 12
array of GPIO descriptors whose values will be read
.IP "array_info" 12
information on applicability of fast bitmap processing path
.IP "value_bitmap" 12
bitmap to store the read values
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the logical values of the GPIOs, i.e. taking their ACTIVE_LOW status
into account.  Return 0 in case of success, else an error code.

This function is to be called from contexts that can sleep.
